ELB: Elastic Load Balancer:
---------------------------		
The 7 OSI Layers: the OSI(open system interactions) model, explain how data moves from one system to another system over the network.
-it used to design, understand, troubleshoot and map network services including aws.

	1.Layer7- Application layer
	what it does, Provides network services to end user applications

	Protocols:
	.HTTP, HTTPS, DNS, FTP
	
	Trouble shoot:
	.website returns 500 error ---> Application issue
	
	2.Layer6- Presentation layer
	What it does, Data formatting, encryption, compresssion
	
	protocols:
	.SSL/TLS (converts http to https)
	
	Trouble shoot:
	.SSL handshakes failure --> Presentation layer issue
	
	3.Layer5-Session layer:
	What it does, Manges sessions between systems
	
	example:
	Authentication sessions
	
	Trouble shoot:
	User logged out frequently--> session issue 
	
	4.Layer4-Transport layer:
	what it does, data transfer and port mangement
	
	Protocols:
	.TCP, UDP
	
	trouble shoot:
	Connection timeout on port 443 --> Transport issue
	
	5.Layer3-Network layer:
	what is does, Routing and IP addressing
	
	Protocol:
	ip(internet protocol)
	
	6.Layer2-Data link
	what it does, MAC addressing and frame delivery
	
	protocols
	Ethernet
	
	7.layer1-Physical layer:
	what it does, transmission of bits
	
	Examples
	.cables, Switches
	
	
What is ELB?
------------
ELB automatically distributes incoming traffic across multiple targets(EC2 instances) to ensure,

		-High availability
		-Scalability
		-Better application performance
		
		
		Example:
		flipkart big billion day sale between jan 24th to 27th
		how many servers required to run my flipkart app?
		can i create EC2 servers manually to my application ?
		To run my application i really dont know how many servers required?
		
		ASG(Autoscaling group): Automatically increases/add and decreases/remove EC2 instances based on incoming application traffic.
		
		min size: 1
		desired capacity: 2
		Max size: 5---------------> Monthly billing(EC2 run time)
		
		
		
		under vertical scaling and horizontal scaling?
		
		what is vertical scaling?
		Ans: Increasing the server resources (CPU/RAM/ROM)---Flipkart (10lakh RPM)
		
		What is horizontal scaling?
		Ans: Increasing no of servers
		
	
Date: 29/12/2025

Autoscaling group components:

1.Launch template:
	-AMI(Amazon machine images-OS(linux/windows)
	-Instance type( choose no of CPU and RAM, ex:t2.micro)
	-Key pair (securely connect instance)
	-Networking (default), subnets, route tables, nat, internetgateway etc
	-EBS (elastic block store), only for EC2, volumes, 16TB (SSD/HDD), Ec2 is accidentlty deleted , data EBS

2.Group Size:
